Sentencas: The electrical conductivity of solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) cathode is one of the most important indices affecting the efficiency of SOFC.
Titulo: MODELING AND PREDICTING THE ELECTRICAL CONDUCTIVITY OF COMPOSITE CATHODE FOR SOLID OXIDE FUEL CELL BY USING SUPPORT VECTOR REGRESSION

Sentencas: In order to improve the performance of fuel cell system, it is advantageous to have accurate model with which one can predict the electrical conductivity.
Titulo: MODELING AND PREDICTING THE ELECTRICAL CONDUCTIVITY OF COMPOSITE CATHODE FOR SOLID OXIDE FUEL CELL BY USING SUPPORT VECTOR REGRESSION

Sentencas: In this paper, a model utilizing support vector regression (SVR) approach combined with particle swarm optimization (PSO) algorithm for its parameter optimization was established to modeling and predicting the electrical conductivity of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-delta-xSm(0.5)Sr(0.5)CoO(3-delta) (BSCF-xSSC) composite cathode under two influence factors, including operating temperature (T) and SSC content (x) in BSCF-xSSC composite cathode.
Titulo: MODELING AND PREDICTING THE ELECTRICAL CONDUCTIVITY OF COMPOSITE CATHODE FOR SOLID OXIDE FUEL CELL BY USING SUPPORT VECTOR REGRESSION

Sentencas: The leave-one-out cross validation (LOOCV) test result by SVR strongly supports that the generalization ability of SVR model is high enough.
Titulo: MODELING AND PREDICTING THE ELECTRICAL CONDUCTIVITY OF COMPOSITE CATHODE FOR SOLID OXIDE FUEL CELL BY USING SUPPORT VECTOR REGRESSION

Sentencas: The absolute percentage error (APE) of 27 samples does not exceed 0.05%.
Titulo: MODELING AND PREDICTING THE ELECTRICAL CONDUCTIVITY OF COMPOSITE CATHODE FOR SOLID OXIDE FUEL CELL BY USING SUPPORT VECTOR REGRESSION

Sentencas: The mean absolute percentage error (MAPE) of all 30 samples is only 0.09% and the correlation coefficient (R-2) as high as 0.999.
Titulo: MODELING AND PREDICTING THE ELECTRICAL CONDUCTIVITY OF COMPOSITE CATHODE FOR SOLID OXIDE FUEL CELL BY USING SUPPORT VECTOR REGRESSION

Sentencas: This investigation suggests that the hybrid PSO-SVR approach may be not only a promising and practical methodology to simulate the properties of fuel cell system, but also a powerful tool to be used for optimal designing or controlling the operating process of a SOFC system.
Titulo: MODELING AND PREDICTING THE ELECTRICAL CONDUCTIVITY OF COMPOSITE CATHODE FOR SOLID OXIDE FUEL CELL BY USING SUPPORT VECTOR REGRESSION
